----------------------------------------------
Installing and compiling
----------------------------------------------

Prerequisites - node.js installed. simple3.0 compiled and environment set

1) Clone the repository
2) cd simple_gui_electron
3) npm install
4) npm run build

----------------------------------------------


----------------------------------------------
Running in standalone mode
----------------------------------------------
1) add simple_gui_electron/bin to your PATH
2) run 'simple'

----------------------------------------------


----------------------------------------------
Running in multiuser mode (only in linux at the moment)
----------------------------------------------

1) add simple_gui_electron/bin to your PATH
2) create users using command 'simple adduser <username> <password>
3) run 'simple multiuser start'
4) connect to the server from google chrome by typing <your hostname or 'localhost'>:8095 in the address bar

You can check the status of the server with 'simple multiuser status'
You can stop the server with 'simple multiuser stop'

----------------------------------------------
Creating tutorials
----------------------------------------------

Tutorials are found in $SIMPLE_PATH/tutorials. These files have an extension of .tut and the filename is interpreted as the tutorial name in the tutorial window launched from the gui.

The contents of the .tut files is in JSON format and is self explanatory from the examples. Create elements within the pages array with title, description and html tags.

To generate the html :
1) in the running gui, generate the view that you want. shift-click will highlight and important elements with a red border.
2) ctrl-x
3) in the .tut file, paste the contents of the clipboard into the html tag. Will be a filename eg. 12345.html

